"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"Musk is able to secure the throne of the richest man, and cryptocurrency can be said to have made great contributions. In addition to Tesla's stock rise, which increased Musk’s wealth, he holds shares of a private company SpaceX, and SpaceX holds Bitcoin. .\\n\\nMusk himself is a cryptocurrency supporter. He not only owns and owns cryptocurrencies such as CX Bitcoin and Dogecoin, but also promotes Tesla to become a cryptocurrency holder and once accepted cryptocurrency payments.\\n\\nIt is reported that Tesla announced in February that it had purchased $1.5 billion worth of Bitcoin. Later in the first quarter, the company cut its Bitcoin position by 10%, increasing its first-quarter earnings by $272 million.\\n\\nAccording to data from [Bitcointreasuries.net](http://Bitcointreasuries.net), Tesla currently holds approximately 43,200 BTC, which is worth approximately $2.5 billion at today's price. This is about 65% higher than the amount paid in February when the company disclosed that its balance sheet increased by $1.5 billion in BTC, or $1 billion. In the second quarter, Tesla sold 10% of its Bitcoin holdings, about 46,000 BTC, and the average price of each token was reported to be about $50,000. In its second-quarter earnings report, the company stated that it received $128 million worth of proceeds from the sale of bitcoin. With the recent rebound in Bitcoin prices, the net profit of Tesla's crypto assets is comparable to Q2 revenue. Tesla reported a net profit of 1.14 billion U.S. dollars in Q2, breaking through the 1 billion U.S. dollar mark for the first time.\\n\\nHowever, due to the large fluctuations in the Bitcoin market, Tesla also suffered huge losses and risks when Bitcoin plummeted.\\n\\nIn July, according to the estimate of Fortune magazine in the United States, as the price of Bitcoin fell below $30,000, Tesla's once-received paper gains of nearly $1.5 billion from investing in Bitcoin have been wiped out. If Bitcoin falls to US$25,000, Tesla will suffer a loss of US$300 million. If it falls to US$20,000, the loss will rise to US$500 million, which is equivalent to almost all of Tesla’s pre-tax profits in the first quarter.\\n\\nHowever, in general, Bitcoin is in a strong bull market this year. Although the market fluctuates too much and brings huge losses, it is ultimately profit-oriented.\\n\\nIn fact, as Bitcoin exceeded $60,000, institutions that previously invested and held Bitcoin received good returns:\\n\\nAccording to Bitcoin Magazine, MicroStrategy's BTC investment has doubled as the price of BTC has risen above US$60,000, and currently reaches US$6.7 billion.\\n\\nTo date, MicroStrategy holds approximately 114,042 bitcoins, with a total purchase price of US$3.16 billion. The average cost price of each bitcoin is US$27,713 (including fees and expenses). The company owns more bitcoins than other listed companies in the world. A lot.\\n\\nIn September of this year, the company’s CEO Michael Saylor announced that it had purchased an additional 5,050 bitcoins with approximately US$242.9 million in cash in the third quarter. There is no plan to sell so far, which means that since the initial investment in bitcoin, MicroStrategy has Has received approximately 3.54 billion U.S. dollars in revenue.\\n\\nAccording to Bitcoin Magazine, the value of Bitcoin investment in Square, a mobile payment company owned by Jack Dorsey, has doubled. The company previously invested $220 million in Bitcoin, which is now worth more than $470 million. So far, Square holds about 8,027 bitcoins, with a total purchase price of 220 million US dollars, and the average price of each bitcoin is 27,407 US dollars, including fees and expenses.\\n\\nThe profit effect stimulates the enthusiasm of institutions. According to incomplete statistics, institutional investors have held more than 1.6 million Bitcoins, accounting for nearly 7.91% of the total supply.\",\"timestamp\":1634580628,\"title\":\"Cryptocurrency is the fundamental power of Musk\"},\"digest\":\"TjwuO1CiIZDKfMAPWKbrEAZL1pzoWx-nutEU4zR5gjA\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0x68a78F3b7Ed88a22e5e158320e0d15B52eDFa312\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"Y8CnCopZNvfVa_t87Y4_UONFdo3yRIrvMHdGAD1bfSw\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"qOcwlY-0aavX-MXXxAjzjSl8A_SY37pT8mBUaVigG5w\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"WZDacFFVkkkdBbul-tri2tey9Jh-gl94RMRC6lX5moq-CBJ7Kym5879BfNvOT3TXeycNYnapfMVd0SLbApfprA\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0x54cb4fab502ecd76f9e0a3e78a52cda47420a425e439284c8568bf5be345fd1703ade28fffd92ca587d308a75b869c7fb52ef1bf775b5ecf4086eb17773ec3cc1c\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize publishing on mirror.xyz from this device using:\\n{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"Y8CnCopZNvfVa_t87Y4_UONFdo3yRIrvMHdGAD1bfSw\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"qOcwlY-0aavX-MXXxAjzjSl8A_SY37pT8mBUaVigG5w\\\"}\",\"algorithm\":{\"name\":\"ECDSA\",\"hash\":\"SHA-256\"}},\"nft\":{},\"version\":\"12-21-2020\",\"originalDigest\":\"TjwuO1CiIZDKfMAPWKbrEAZL1pzoWx-nutEU4zR5gjA\"}"